Reporter: Jacob Bowser
Locality: Property of 544 Northwest Road, Canterbury NH and neighboring properties. Report submitted by owner of the former property.
Comments: Infestation is worst in an area of sparse white pines, but the entire infestation spreads out very far from the major parts. There is a second area of conifers that is becoming infested. Less dense areas include deciduous and mixed forest areas, especially on the edges of fields and clearings. An effort is being made to remove the species in the densest area. Around 2500 square feet of the densest area has been cleared of buckthorn. This was and still is being done using the Root Talon, a tool specifically designed for the removal of shallow-root invasives like buckthorn. Progress is certainly being made, but the boundaries of the infestation are growing too fast to keep up with.
